President Muhammadu Buhari and nine All Progressives Congress (APC) Governors are meeting in his Daura country home in Katsina State. They are Governors Aminu Masari (Katsina); Abdullahi Ganduje (Kano); Abubakar Bagudu (Kebbi); Abubakar Bello (Niger); Abdullahi Sule (Nasarawa); Hope Uzodinma (Imo); Kayode Fayemi (Ekiti); Simon Lalong (Plateau) and Nasir El-Rufai (Kaduna).   Ganduje frees 90 inmates in celebration of Sallah     Nigeria under siege of terrorists, bandits – ACF     Nigeria faring better under Buhari – Presidency   They were led to the meeting by the Chairman Progressives Governor’s Forum Abubakar Bagudu of Kebbi state. They drove into Daura’s private residence of the President at about 1 pm shortly after which the meeting started. Details Shortly….